== 票房 ==
《生命中的美好缺憾》於北美收益賺得$124,900,000美元，其他地區賺得$182,300,000美元，以及全球賺得$307,200,000美元，對比12,000,000美元的製作預算<ref name="BOM"/>。

在北美，電影的收益自《我們的星星之夜（The Night Before Our Stars）》的活動獲得提升，門票售價高達$25美元的高端價格的活動。該活動包括電影的放映及跟演員和工作人員的同步的問答環節，當中包括活莉、果特、沃爾夫和格林<ref name=BOMJune05>{{cite web|last=Subers|first=Ray|title=Forecast: 'Fault' to Push Cruise to the 'Edge' of the Box Office|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/news/?id=3853|publisher=[[Box_Office_Mojo|Box Office Mojo]]|date=2014-06-05}}</ref>。電影於周四晚上的放映中賺得$820萬美元的收入，而開畫當日收益得到$26,100,000美元<ref name=BOMJune07>{{cite web|last=Subers|first=Ray|title=Friday Report: 'Fault' Shines, 'Edge' Flatlines on Friday|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/news/?id=3854|publisher=[[Box_Office_Mojo|Box Office Mojo]]|date=2014-06-07}}</ref><ref name="#3"/>。在開畫周末，電影從3,173家影院賺得48,002,573美元的收益，平均每部電影賺得$15,128美元，成為北美票房冠軍<ref name="#4"/>。

在北美以外的地區，《生命中的美好缺憾》的開畫周末，從17個市場的2,892張屏幕中賺得$16,590,000美元位列第四，繼《[[異空戰士|異空戰士]]》的$81,000,000美元，《[[梅爾菲森特|黑魔后]]》的$61,700,000美元，及《[[變種特攻：未來同盟戰|變種特攻：未來同盟戰]]》的$41,100,000美元之後。電影在[[巴西|巴西]]，[[墨西哥|墨西哥]]和[[澳大利亞|澳大利亞]]的收入最高，分別為$5,800,000美元、$3,800,000美元及$3,700,000美元<ref>{{cite web | url = http://deadline.com/2014/06/intl-box-office-edge-of-tomorrow-no-1-with-82m-fault-in-our-stars-shines-in-brazil-mexico-oz-maleficent-adds-59-7m-x-men-crosses-100m-in-china-more-2-786479/ | title = Intl Box Office: ‘Edge Of Tomorrow’ No. 1 With $81M; ‘Fault In Our Stars’ Shines Bright In Brazil, Mexico, Oz; ‘Maleficent’ Adds $61.7M; ‘X-Men’ Crosses $100M In China; More | author = Nancy Tartaglione | publisher = Deadline.com | date = 2014-06-09 | accessdate = 2014-12-09 | archive-date = 2020-04-20 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200420134731/https://deadline.com/2014/06/intl-box-office-edge-of-tomorrow-no-1-with-82m-fault-in-our-stars-shines-in-brazil-mexico-oz-maleficent-adds-59-7m-x-men-crosses-100m-in-china-more-2-786479/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>。隨後一星期，電影從40個市場賺得收益$16,100,000美元，再次保持在第4位的位置<ref>{{cite web | url = http://deadline.com/2014/06/intl-box-office-godzilla-thrashes-again-with-38m-weekend-led-by-china-how-to-train-your-dragon-2-fires-up-24-8m-more-788313/ | title = Final Int’l Box Office: ‘Godzilla’ Thrashes Again With $38.4M Weekend Led By China; ‘How To Train Your Dragon 2′ Fires Up $24.4M; ‘Fault’ On Fire In Brazil | author = Nancy Tartaglione | publisher = Deadline.com | date = 2014-06-16 | accessdate = 2014-12-09 | archive-date = 2021-03-16 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210316103522/https://deadline.com/2014/06/intl-box-office-godzilla-thrashes-again-with-38m-weekend-led-by-china-how-to-train-your-dragon-2-fires-up-24-8m-more-788313/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

